This Starbucks opened around 5a.m. At the time I use to frequent it most I was homeless. This was the fall/winter of 2009.The start of my day to organize my thoughts for my survival happened at this Starbucks on many a day.I'd order my beverage and then get myself prepared to face the world determined that homelessness was just a temporary status.On one occassion,it was well below freezing (-5 plus wind chill) and I was barely able to make it to this Starbucks from where I had slept outside the previous night.It took nearly 3 hours just to stop my body from shivering even with hot beverages and the warmth of the room.The staff was always courteous and professional to every person who entered.I doubt they ever knew I was homeless as a point of fact,but I did observe them treating each customer with the same amount of professionalism.As little in resources as I had at the time,I made sure to always tip my Baristas. On my trips back to D.C. I still frequent this Starbucks as a reminder of how the wheel has turned in my life.
